  "name": "Aeon Stone (Black Pearl)",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>This black pearl sparkles with light. The resonant power allows you to cast <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.R9xqCBblkS5KE4y7]{Sending}</em> once per day.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">R</span> envision</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> you are targeted by a mental effect</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You receive a +4 status bonus to your saving throw against the triggering effect.</p>\n<p>Whether or not your save is successful, the aeon stone attempts a counteract check at [[/r {1d20+30} #Counteract]]{1d20+30} to immediately reflect a copy of the effect back at the originator, targeting it using the creature's own relevant statistics but controlling the effect as if you had cast it.</p>\n<p>Every time you activate this aeon stone, attempt a @Check[type:flat|dc:5]. On a failure, the stone shatters and loses its magical properties forever.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-effects.Item.p2aGtovaY1feytws]{Effect: Aeon Stone (Black Pearl)}</p>"
